H0.text: In the human body, what is the common name for the 'Talus bone'. Heel Bone

H1.text: In the human body, what is the common name for the 'Talus bone'. Ankle Joint

H2.text: In the human body, what is the common name for the 'Talus bone'. Foot Bone

H3.text: In the human body, what is the common name for the 'Talus bone'. Ancle

A4.text: The talus is one of the group of foot bones known as the tarsus.

A5.text: The talus (; Latin for ankle or ankle bone; pl. : tali), talus bone, astragalus (), or ankle bone is one of the group of foot bones known as the tarsus.

A6.text: The main bones of the ankle region are the talus (in the foot), the tibia, and fibula (both in the leg).
